Appreciation post for my love, soulmate and fiancé @dijonnaise911!!!

Thank you for being my creative accomplice, my protector, my family, best friend, my lovey… thank you for making me laugh so hard I have to pull the car over!!

Thank you for challenging me to always reach my highest peak and listen to my gut. 

Thank you for believing in me when I crumble. This year wasn’t easy… 

Thank you for celebrating my fluff and my freckles and for loving Pete, Frizz, Ram, Emilia, Hannah, Aiden, Bailey, Bandit, Roxy, My mom, Sunny and Luna like you do. 

I love you forever and past that. Excited to continue our adventures from the dunes of Abu Dhabi to the shores of Italy to a taco shack in Georgia... Thank you for a beautiful life. I know from my own parents that love can escape some… I don’t take a minute with you for granted. ❤️

2022 had given me many unexpected blessings and many unexpected losses. 

I am grateful for the amazing and beautiful people and experiences that walked into my life this year, and I am grateful for the people and things that walked out. I was able to see things this year that I couldn’t see before, and now I can reflect on it. 

Regardless of what obstacles are in front of you, or the people that are or are not standing by your side, blaze forward with faith and abandon. On the other side of fear there is a limitless version of yourself waiting to meet you.

Day 1: Grateful and humbled to have attended the opening of the @nmacc.india Cultural Centre in Mumbai as a guest of the beautiful and deeply inspiring Ambani family in Mumbai this weekend. Thank you for bringing me to India to celebrate with you 🙏🏽❤️

The Nita Mukesh Ambani Cultural Centre, in the words of Nita is "An ode to our nation, the Cultural Centre aims to preserve and promote Indian arts. I hope our spaces nurture and inspire talent, bringing together communities from across India and the globe." 

It was inspiring to see Isha, Nita and Mukesh bringing the world together to empower and celebrate India: a country, whose both art, and spirituality, have impacted my life’s journey deeply (thank you Sadhguru and Deepak 🙏🏽)

I have never been brought to tears by a musical until watching “The Great Indian Musical” by Feroz Kahn… but leave it to the Ambanis to curate an epic experience and bring the house down. As a fellow former dancer myself, Nita showing me what is possible when you continue to move in your purpose, touched my soul.

Thank you @jilldemling for letting me tag along. Truly one of the best weekends of my life, and wouldn’t have been if I wasn’t by you and @karen_mulligan’s side experiencing it all… Jill, you have a way of bringing incredible people together in a way that illuminates them. Anyone would be lucky to work with you, but I’m especially lucky to call you and Karen my friends. Mumbai Musketeers for life. ✨🥹

It is truly what you do with your art, and how you use your gifts to make this world a better place that really matter. 

Wearing (yes again 😂) my talented friend @naeemkhannyc 
Cool girl hair by super cool girl @jrmellocastro 
Forever accomplices in wearable art: @marcodl82 @parischea 
Jewelry from the streets of the Mumbai marketplace: Chor Bazaar

Day 2: To be continued…

#NMACC

Day 2: The @nmacc.india’s “India in Fashion”exhibition curated by the fantastic brilliant mind that is @hamishbowles. No one does an exhibit (or wears lavender) quite like you do my friend.

Seeing the exquisite pieces curated in such an expansive exhibit, truly solidified my understanding of how deep the inspiration of India (from embroidered fabrics to classic structures) in design goes. 

Hamish… I will forever cherish chatting archive, storage temperatures and fashion history with you. Thank you for all of the incredibly thoughtful work that you put into yet another one of your history making exhibits. 

Wearing custom @gauravguptaofficial by @ggpanther who is making Hollywood history at this moment in time. Gaurav merges indigenous Indian construction and embellishing techniques with his idea of the future. It is truly a privilege to wear your art sir. Thank you, and see you on the dance floor... 🙏🏽 

Thank you to my bestie @boseh1 for making sure this moment was everything it could be, and that I could represent Gaurav and his vision in its entirety. You are the Karen to my Jill (will explain later) and I love you more than Aam Papad!!!!!

Day 3:  Our last day at the @nmacc.india art show, curated by Ranjit Hoskote and Jeffrey Deitch.

My jacket was made by designer Supriti Chatterjee from her graduate design collection at the @ESEDSSchoolofDesign in Kolkata, India. 

It is the first International design school in India to address the urgency of integrating ethical design processes and the theme of sustainable design into its curriculum. 

Supriti Chatterjee comes from a humble background from Sreerampore, West Bengal where her father works in a shoe factory. 

Her work is a tribute to the legendary Bengali comic artist, writer and illustrator Narayan Debnath who passed away in 2022. He had created the comic strips like Bantul the great, Handa Bhonda and Nonte Phonte. 

Oh my birthday twin @boseh1 If only you were as much of a ham as me, we would be identical 😂

We sat on your couch, and talked about what it actually means to be invited to come and celebrate the opening of the @nmacc.india cultural center in Mumbai. 

What do I have to offer this experience? How can I leave India having had given, and not just received?

So I asked you to help find me a young fashion student in India, from a small town. You suggested the Eseds fashion school in Kolkata, where you are from… I wanted to showcase someone who could be recognized for their work and creativity. And you found her… 

This. THIS is how I wish to contribute as an artist, and overall person in my life. 

Thank you for holding my hand and leading me closer to who I am. As I have found from this weekend, your best friends will always be the ones who will guide you closer to your truth.

I am writing this from the refugee camp… so sending so much love to everyone who came out to @comicconcapetown for helping us raise so much.

UNHCR in tha building!!

Just returned home from Ethiopia with the UN @Refugees Agency, where we are gearing up for our latest appeal initiative. But before I get into it, I wanted to express my deepest gratitude to my UNHCR family. 

The hard work, sacrifice, tenacity, perseverance, and HOPE that this agency represents is remarkable. 

Thank you @danamhughes @zechjoma @Meliket2019 @crvenkovicneven @msanyuosire @amychristian @rems_werema @mulugeta_r and everyone at UNHCR for everything you do and did to ensure this was a successful mission. 

It's now been over 10 years working with this heroic organization, and I'm just getting started. I pray I have at least 50 more years in me, dedicated to fighting for the support of refugees globally. My dream is to see the day when the last camp closes, and the world can coexist in peace and acceptance. 🇺🇳✨🇪🇹

Supported @refugees @iefta_org’s refugee voices in film event with @danamhughes during the Cannes Film Festival. IEFTA supports emerging filmmakers in developing countries.

For the sixth year, IEFTA has collaborated with the United Nations Refugee Agency (UNHCR). The program presents filmmakers — a number of them refugees themselves — who are documenting the experiences of those forced to flee from violence, famine or political oppression.

The UN @Refugees Agency and IEFTA provide filmmaking tools and training to those affected. Refugees speak out about loss and desperation, but also resilience and hope.

The crisis in #Sudan hasn’t had anywhere near the coverage it deserves.⁣
⁣

Hope is being able to see that there is light despite all of the darkness.” - Desmond Tutu
 
I recently visited Ethiopia, a country generously hosting nearly 1 million refugees and asylum-seekers, now facing equally urgent challenges. The impact of one of the most severe droughts on record, followed by historic rains that have washed away roads, livestock and crops, have left refugees and their host communities in a dire situation.
 
In just the last few months, conflict in neighboring Somalia has caused around 100,000 people to flee across the border… Most are women and children, arriving exhausted, hungry and traumatized. New arrivals have been largely welcomed by Ethiopian host communities, doing their part to help. But they urgently need more support.
 
Funding levels for the Ethiopia operation remain critically low. Right now, shelter, water, and other life-saving aid is urgently needed to help these displaced families.
 
We’ve seen the world come together before to show solidarity with people who have lost everything through no fault of their own. We can’t turn away now. The people forced to flee I’ve met here deserve and need the world’s attention and support.  Please donate now and join me in showing solidarity by helping to provide critical live-saving assistance Every single dollar counts and can make a world of difference. 
 
Click the link in my bio to donate now and support @refugees.

Today is #WorldRefugeeDay. But solidarity with refugees is about much more than one day. Refugees like my friend Aqlima are more than statistics. They are talented human beings with their own stories, hopes and dreams.

Displacement can happen to any one of us as a result of war, violence, drought, climate change and more. @Refugees works hard to ensure that everyone has the right not just to survive, but to thrive… for ourselves, our children, and our community. We are in this together.

That’s why today I’m honored as a UNHCR Goodwill Ambassador to pass the phone to Aqlima, who was forced to flee Somalia for Ethiopia. I’m excited to share more about her story in the coming weeks.

Grateful for the chance to join forces with @danamhughes, the incredible Deputy Head of Communications for @refugees at @collisionconfhq in Toronto.

Our discussion at the event covered vital topics like climate change, digital inclusion, and empowering refugees in their journey to rebuild their lives. It's crucial to address the barriers caused by limited technology access and online protection in the digital age. 

#WithRefugees

Thank you to my incredible team and team Vogue for this beautiful shoot. I am truly humbled and honored.

Growing up rummaging through second-hand dollar clothes, altering and patching them together, Vogue became my representation of possibility. It represented a world of abundance, where I could flip thru pages of fabulous women, empowered, and using fashion as a form of self expression and freedom, a privilege that many around the world yearn for but are denied due to circumstances beyond their control.

So, in this moment, I want to scream my gratitude to the skies for the incredible team that made this little girl’s dreams possible. 

Thank you for seeing the fire within me and fanning it into flames. Your dedication, creativity, and unwavering support have forever imprinted on me.  You've lifted me up when I stumbled and reminded me of my own strength when doubt threatened to consume me.

So… Dream boldly. Shatter expectations and inspire a world that knows no limits.

Gracias por todo… mi familia 💕

It was an immense honor to represent the UN @Refugees Agency and speak at @oneyoungworld, alongside exceptional leaders from around the world who are actively driving positive global change. 

I also had the privilege of sharing the stage with @unitednations Assistant Secretary-General and UNHCR Assistant High Commissioner for Protection, the brilliant Gillian Triggs. Gillian oversees UNHCR’s protection work in support of millions of refugees, asylum-seekers, and those who have been forcibly displaced within their own country and stateless.

I want to express my heartfelt gratitude to @danamhughes and @clairecangelle for orchestrating such a remarkable conversation.

During the event, I had the privilege of engaging in discussions on crucial topics such as supporting climate refugees, enhancing refugee welfare, amplifying refugee voices, and exploring strategies for representation.

One Young World stands as the preeminent global youth leadership Summit, bringing together individuals who shape the future of our world to address humanity's most pressing challenges. The Summit serves as an inspiring convergence of thought leaders and change makers. Thank you for the incredible opportunity!
Thank you @ccfpeace 🙏🏽

It is bittersweet to be recognized by @ccfpeace with a peace award amidst one of the most tumultuous periods in history. We have all been feeling the deep grief and heartbreak of the innocent Israeli and Palestinian lives that have been lost. In recent weeks, we have witnessed the distressing violence and unimaginable horrors unfolding in Israel and Gaza. It’s during times of fear that soft power is so often undermined. 

To be recognized by the Community for Peace alongside purpose-driven creatives Liev Schreiber, Ben Silverman, Gustavo Lopez, and Aaron Rosenberg is truly an honor. I’m humbled and deeply grateful to be presented with this award by my friend, Holocaust survivor Yetta Kane. 

The arts have the unique ability to transcend language and cultural barriers. While it cannot stop bloodshed, it can and must foster empathy, encourage dialogue, and bring people closer together. These are the values that promote long-term peace. 

In our everyday lives, we all have the power to lead with empathy and promote the dignity of life for all. We can choose not to confuse the people with the organizations that govern them. We can choose not to confuse support for a group of innocent people as an expression of hate or oppression for another. Solutions are not based on violence. 

I believe that we can all channel our passions and pain towards the protection and support of the vulnerable and innocent. That has been my lifelong dedication to human rights globally and I will continue to do my part.

We can all be part of the solution and come together in peace. 

It is possible.

This week the UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR) is hosting the largest gathering in support of @refugees - the Global #RefugeeForum. It’s a moment of solidarity #WithRefugees. And, it needs to be a turning point in how we welcome refugees everywhere. UNHCR provides protection and life-saving services to refugees around the world, but we cannot do it alone. As a global community, we need to work together to increase access to solutions, improve conditions in countries of origin, and enhance refugee self-reliance. Refugees don’t want handouts, they want the tools they need to rebuild their lives and thrive on their own two feet. Follow @refugees to hear the latest on all the pledges that will be made in the coming days.
